<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-03-06T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-03-06T08:00:00-05:00" n="507" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d507">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.51632 National City Bank/8:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Morgan</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de
                                        Janeiro</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-03-06T10:00:00-03:00">March 6, 1930—10
                                a.m.</date><lb/>[Received 10:15 a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>8. Department’s telegram number 9, March 5, 5 p.m. My telegram number 7,
                            March 4, 5 p.m., did not imply that the question of filing a bond
                            instead of depositing securities or cash was settled. Matter is still
                            under consideration.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Morgan</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>